overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  sleep questionnaire application. The agent systematically navigated through
  the application, testing the questionnaire flow, form validation, conditional
  fields, and report generation. It also interacted with various API endpoints,
  including PDF generation, responses, and admin login, verifying their
  functionality and error handling. During this process, the agent encountered
  and resolved some confusion regarding navigation and state updates,
  attributing them to potential React rendering timing issues. Ultimately, the
  agent provided a detailed summary of its findings, highlighting correctly
  working features and noting minor issues such as ESLint warnings and an
  outdated page title, along with actionable recommendations. The user then
  requested to proceed with fixing these identified issues.
